---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="STEM & Projects"
  description="Maren Stokes' journey in coding, mathematics, physics, and machine learning."
>
  <div class="projects-page">
    <SectionHeading
      title="STEM & Projects"
      subtitle="My journey through code, mathematics, and the pursuit of understanding"
    />

    <section class="journey-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Coding & STEM Journey</h2>
      <div class="journey-content">
        <p class="lead">
          I've been coding since <strong>4th grade</strong>, and technology has always been
          part of how I think and solve problems. What started as simple curiosity and
          experimentation has grown into a deeper passion for understanding how we can use
          computation and mathematics to explain and shape the world around us.
        </p>

        <p>
          Over time, that early curiosity grew into a deeper interest in <strong>applied math,
          physics, and machine learning</strong>, especially how abstract ideas explain
          real-world systems. I love the challenge of taking theoretical concepts and finding
          ways to apply them to solve meaningful problems.
        </p>

        <p>
          Through advanced coursework at LASA, two summers at the <strong>UT Austin Computer
          Science Machine Learning Camps</strong>, and countless hours of independent exploration,
          I've developed not just technical skills, but a way of thinking â€” one that values
          precision, creativity, and the connection between theory and practice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="interests-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Areas I'm Especially Interested In</h2>

      <div class="interests-grid">
        <div class="interest-card">
          <div class="interest-icon">âˆ‘</div>
          <h3>Applied Mathematics</h3>
          <p>
            Using mathematical frameworks to model complex systems, solve optimization problems,
            and find elegant solutions to real-world challenges. I love the way math provides
            a universal language for understanding patterns and structures.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <div class="interest-icon">âš›</div>
          <h3>Physics & Understanding the Universe</h3>
          <p>
            Exploring the fundamental laws that govern our reality â€” from classical mechanics
            to the behavior of complex systems. Physics has taught me to think rigorously and
            see the world through a mathematical lens.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <div class="interest-icon">ðŸ¤–</div>
          <h3>Machine Learning & Intelligent Systems</h3>
          <p>
            Building systems that can learn, adapt, and make decisions. I'm fascinated by how
            we can use algorithms and data to create intelligence, and how ML can be applied
            to everything from scientific research to solving societal challenges.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <div class="interest-icon">ðŸ”¬</div>
          <h3>Connecting Theory to Real-World Impact</h3>
          <p>
            I'm driven by the intersection of theoretical understanding and practical application.
            The most exciting work happens when abstract ideas become tools that make a
            meaningful difference in the world.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-showcase">
      <h2 class="section-title">Recent Project: Building This Portfolio Website</h2>

      <div class="project-card featured">
        <div class="project-header">
          <h3>Portfolio Website with AI-Assisted Development</h3>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="tech-tag">Astro</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">TypeScript</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">GitHub Pages</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Claude AI</span>
            <span class="date-tag">January 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-content">
          <h4>Overview</h4>
          <p>
            I built this personal portfolio website as a hands-on project to showcase my work and learn
            modern web development practices. The project combined technical implementation with design
            thinking, using AI tools to accelerate development while maintaining creative control.
          </p>

          <h4>My Role & Process</h4>
          <p><strong>Planning & Design:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Created a comprehensive website plan outlining structure, content, and design direction</li>
            <li>Designed a warm, nature-inspired color palette contrasting typical "cold" STEM aesthetics</li>
            <li>Chose soft pastels (honey yellow, sage green, blush pink) to create an approachable feel</li>
            <li>Selected typography (Playfair Display + DM Sans) for elegance and readability</li>
            <li>Organized content across 6 pages: Home, About, Academics, Activities, STEM & Projects, Contact</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Development Decisions:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Selected Astro as the framework for its performance and simplicity</li>
            <li>Chose GitHub Pages for free, reliable hosting</li>
            <li>Designed reusable component architecture (Layout, Sidebar, Card, SectionHeading)</li>
            <li>Provided detailed CSS theme specifications for consistent styling</li>
            <li>Reviewed and approved all generated code before deployment</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Collaboration with Claude Code:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Used Claude Code CLI to accelerate development with AI assistance</li>
            <li>Provided detailed prompts and specifications for each feature</li>
            <li>Reviewed generated components and pages for quality and accuracy</li>
            <li>Iterated on design details (removed emojis, adjusted navigation, refined content)</li>
            <li>Debugged deployment issues (GitHub Pages configuration, base path routing)</li>
          </ul>

          <h4>Technical Implementation</h4>
          <p><strong>What Claude Built:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Initialized Astro project with proper folder structure</li>
            <li>Implemented global CSS with design system (colors, typography, spacing)</li>
            <li>Created Layout component with sidebar integration</li>
            <li>Built Sidebar navigation with active page detection and base URL support</li>
            <li>Developed reusable Card and SectionHeading components</li>
            <li>Generated all 6 pages with provided content from source materials</li>
            <li>Configured GitHub Actions workflow for automated deployment</li>
            <li>Fixed routing issues for GitHub Pages project deployment</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Technical Stack:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Astro v5.16.6 (static site generation)</li>
            <li><strong>Languages:</strong> TypeScript, HTML, CSS</li>
            <li><strong>Fonts:</strong> Google Fonts (Playfair Display, DM Sans)</li>
            <li><strong>Deployment:</strong> GitHub Actions â†’ GitHub Pages</li>
            <li><strong>Version Control:</strong> Git/GitHub</li>
          </ul>

          <h4>Key Features</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Responsive design that works on desktop, tablet, and mobile</li>
            <li>Fixed sidebar navigation with smooth transitions and active states</li>
            <li>Warm, nature-inspired design system with botanical gradients</li>
            <li>Reusable component architecture for maintainability</li>
            <li>Automated deployment pipeline (push to main â†’ auto-deploy)</li>
            <li>SEO-friendly meta tags and semantic HTML</li>
          </ul>

          <h4>Challenges & Solutions</h4>
          <p><strong>GitHub Pages Configuration:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Challenge:</em> Initial 404 errors due to incorrect base path configuration</li>
            <li><em>Solution:</em> Configured Astro's base URL to match GitHub project page structure</li>
            <li><em>Learning:</em> Understanding the difference between user pages and project pages on GitHub</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Navigation Routing:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Challenge:</em> Links pointing to root domain instead of project subdirectory</li>
            <li><em>Solution:</em> Updated Sidebar and Card components to use BASE_URL environment variable</li>
            <li><em>Learning:</em> Importance of relative vs absolute paths in deployed applications</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Design Iteration:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Challenge:</em> Initial design had unnecessary decorative elements</li>
            <li><em>Solution:</em> Removed emojis, simplified contact page, cleaned up sidebar</li>
            <li><em>Learning:</em> Less is moreâ€”focusing on content over decoration</li>
          </ul>

          <h4>What I Learned</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Modern Web Frameworks:</strong> Hands-on experience with Astro's component-based architecture</li>
            <li><strong>Design Systems:</strong> Creating cohesive visual identities with CSS variables</li>
            <li><strong>AI-Assisted Development:</strong> How to effectively collaborate with AI tools while maintaining creative control</li>
            <li><strong>DevOps Basics:</strong> Setting up CI/CD pipelines with GitHub Actions</li>
            <li><strong>Problem Solving:</strong> Debugging deployment issues and understanding web hosting configurations</li>
            <li><strong>Project Management:</strong> Breaking down complex projects into manageable tasks</li>
          </ul>

          <h4>Reflection</h4>
          <p>
            This project taught me that effective use of AI tools isn't about letting them do all the workâ€”it's
            about clear communication, thoughtful planning, and maintaining creative vision. I provided the
            direction, made all design decisions, and reviewed every line of code. Claude accelerated the
            implementation, but the choices that make this site unique were mine.
          </p>
          <p>
            Building this website reinforced my interest in the intersection of design and engineering. The
            technical implementation matters, but so does creating an experience that feels warm, personal,
            and authenticâ€”something that reflects who I am beyond just my technical skills.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="future-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Looking Ahead</h2>
      <div class="future-content">
        <p>
          I'm continuing to build projects, explore deeply, and learn as much as I can â€”
          especially as I prepare for college and beyond. My goal is to work at the
          intersection of mathematics, physics, and computer science, contributing to
          research and technology that pushes the boundaries of what's possible.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .projects-page {
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .journey-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
  }

  .journey-content {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .journey-content p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .journey-content .lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }

  .journey-content strong {
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .interests-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
  }

  .interests-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .interest-card {
    background-color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    border: 1px solid rgba(74, 74, 74, 0.08);
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
  }

  .interest-card:hover {
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .interest-icon {
    font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .interest-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .interest-card p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Project Showcase */
  .project-showcase {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
  }

  .project-card {
    background-color: var(--color-white);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    border: 1px solid rgba(74, 74, 74, 0.08);
  }

  .project-card.featured {
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-honey);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-white) 0%, rgba(255, 242, 211, 0.3) 100%);
  }

  .project-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent-honey);
  }

  .project-header h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-main);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .project-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .tech-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-md);
    background: #FAD4D4;
    color: var(--text-main);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    border-radius: 999px;
  }

  .date-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-md);
    background: var(--accent-blush);
    color: var(--text-main);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    border-radius: 999px;
  }

  .project-content h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-main);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .project-content p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .project-content ul {
    margin: var(--space-md) 0 var(--space-lg);
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .project-content li {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .project-content strong {
    color: var(--text-main);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .project-content em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-main);
  }

  .project-links {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-soft);
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .future-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
  }

  .future-content {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .future-content > p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .journey-content .lead,
    .future-content > p {
      font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    }

    .journey-content p {
      font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    }

    .interests-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    }

    .interest-card {
      padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    }

    .interest-icon {
      font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    }

    .project-card {
      padding: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .project-header h3 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    }

    .project-links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
